        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 8:59PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 859 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Dillwyn, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Cumberland and Guinea Mills around 925 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Hatchers, Trents Mill,
Angola, Ashby, Oak Forest, Provost, Rodophil, McRae, Clinton, and
Tamworth.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
